  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Spray a baking dish with cooking spray.",
    "Tear the brioche into 1-inch pieces and scatter in the baking dish.",
    "Drizzle Nutella over the brioche.",
    "Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes.",
    "While the brioche mixture is baking, toast almonds in tandoor at 400°F (200°C) for 5 minutes.",
    "Once the almonds are toasted, chop and stir into the Nutella mixture.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together egg, almond milk, cheddar, a pinch of salt, and a pinch of tandoor powder.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the Nutella mixture in the baking dish.",
    "Top with fresh berries and drizzle with brown sugar.",
    "Bake for an additional 15 minutes, or until puffed and golden brown.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool for 10 minutes before serving."
  ],
